    "/v1/ws/market/price": {
      "get": {
        "tags": ["Market Data"],
        "summary": "Stream Current Price Over WebSocket",
        "description": "Upgrades the HTTP connection to a WebSocket and streams latest ticker price updates as JSON text frames. This endpoint is documented manually because WebSocket upgrade routes are not generated from protobuf HTTP annotations.\n\nConnect to `ws://{host}/v1/ws/market/price?exchange=2&symbol=BTC%2FUSDT` or `wss://{host}/v1/ws/market/price?exchange=2&symbol=BTC%2FUSDT`.\n\nAfter the `101 Switching Protocols` response, there is no HTTP response body. The client receives WebSocket text frames shaped as:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"symbol\": \"BTC/USDT\",\n  \"price\": 68420.12,\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-06-07T10:15:30Z\"\n}\n```\n\nIf streaming cannot continue after upgrade, the server may send an error frame before closing the connection:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"error\": \"failed to watch ticker\"\n}\n```",
        "operationId": "MarketData_WebSocketCurrentPrice",
        "produces": ["application/json"],
        "parameters": [
          {
            "name": "exchange",
            "in": "query",
            "description": "Numeric exchange identifier from the Exchange enum, for example 1 for Tokocrypto or 2 for Binance.",
            "required": true,
            "type": "integer",
            "format": "int32"
          },
          {
            "name": "symbol",
            "in": "query",
            "description": "Trading pair symbol, for example BTC/USDT.",
            "required": true,
            "type": "string"
          }
        ],
        "responses": {
          "101": {
            "description": "Switching Protocols. The HTTP response has no JSON body; after upgrade, the WebSocket sends PriceStreamMessage JSON text frames.",
            "headers": {
              "Upgrade": {
                "type": "string",
                "description": "websocket"
              },
              "Connection": {
                "type": "string",
                "description": "Upgrade"
              }
            },
            "x-websocket-message-schema": {
              "$ref": "#/definitions/PriceStreamMessage"
            },
            "x-websocket-message-example": {
              "symbol": "BTC/USDT",
              "price": 68420.12,
              "timestamp": "2026-06-07T10:15:30Z"
            },
            "x-websocket-error-schema": {
              "$ref": "#/definitions/WebSocketErrorMessage"
            },
            "x-websocket-error-example": {
              "error": "failed to watch ticker"
            }
          },
          "400": {
            "description": "Invalid request parameters before upgrade, such as missing exchange or symbol. Returned as a plain HTTP error response."
          },
          "401": {
            "description": "Unauthorized when authentication is enabled."
          },
          "500": {
            "description": "WebSocket upgrade or exchange streaming error."
          }
        },
        "x-websocket-message": {
          "$ref": "#/definitions/PriceStreamMessage"
        }
      }
    },
    "/v1/ws/market/orderbook": {
      "get": {
        "tags": ["Market Data"],
        "summary": "Stream Order Book Over WebSocket",
        "description": "Upgrades the HTTP connection to a WebSocket and streams real-time order book (bids and asks) updates as JSON text frames.\n\nConnect to `ws://{host}/v1/ws/market/orderbook?exchange=2&symbol=BTC%2FUSDT&limit=20`.\n\nSupported exchanges stream via CCXT `watchOrderBook`; unsupported exchanges fall back to REST polling every 1 second. After the `101 Switching Protocols` response, the client receives WebSocket text frames shaped as:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"symbol\": \"BTC/USDT\",\n  \"bids\": [[68000.5, 1.2], [67999.0, 0.5]],\n  \"asks\": [[68001.0, 0.8], [68002.5, 1.0]],\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-06-08T12:55:50Z\"\n}\n```",
        "operationId": "MarketData_WebSocketOrderBook",
        "produces": ["application/json"],
        "parameters": [
          {
            "name": "exchange",
            "in": "query",
            "description": "Numeric exchange identifier from the Exchange enum, for example 2 for Binance.",
            "required": true,
            "type": "integer",
            "format": "int32"
          },
          {
            "name": "symbol",
            "in": "query",
            "description": "Trading pair symbol, for example BTC/USDT.",
            "required": true,
            "type": "string"
          },
          {
            "name": "limit",
            "in": "query",
            "description": "Number of top bids and asks to return per update. Defaults to 20, max 100.",
            "required": false,
            "type": "integer",
            "format": "int32",
            "default": 20
          }
        ],
        "responses": {
          "101": {
            "description": "Switching Protocols. After upgrade, the WebSocket sends OrderBookStreamMessage JSON text frames.",
            "x-websocket-message-schema": {
              "$ref": "#/definitions/OrderBookStreamMessage"
            },
            "x-websocket-message-example": {
              "symbol": "BTC/USDT",
              "bids": [
                [68000.5, 1.2],
                [67999.0, 0.5]
              ],
              "asks": [
                [68001.0, 0.8],
                [68002.5, 1.0]
              ],
              "timestamp": "2026-06-08T12:55:50Z"
            },
            "x-websocket-error-schema": {
              "$ref": "#/definitions/WebSocketErrorMessage"
            }
          },
          "400": {
            "description": "Invalid request parameters before upgrade."
          },
          "401": {
            "description": "Unauthorized when authentication is enabled."
          },
          "500": {
            "description": "WebSocket upgrade or exchange streaming error."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "/examples/websocket": {
      "get": {
        "tags": ["Examples"],
        "summary": "Open WebSocket Candlestick Example",
        "description": "Serves the browser example used to load historical OHLCV candles and connect to the WebSocket latest price stream from the same HTTP origin. Open this route instead of the local file path to avoid browser CORS restrictions.",
